data.title: Born on November 22, 1965
data.meta_description: Interesting facts and milestones for people born on November 22, 1965. Read this if you are born on November 22, 1965.
data.text:
Interesting facts and milestones for people born on November 22, 1965. This page is all about people that were born on November 22, 1965. We have tons of facts, milestones, and information so sit back, relax, and enjoy!

The day you were born

Of course you know that you were born on November 22, 1965, but do you know what day of the week you were born? Well, you will now. You were born on a Monday.

1000 days old

Most kids no longer need to wear diapers by the time they are 1000 days old. At that age, most girls and boys can also walk. You are definitely not a toddler anymore at this point. Your 1000 day birthday is on August 18, 1968.

3000 days old

Your 3000 day birthday comes a couple of months after your 8th birthday and is a cool day to celebrate. Most kids are in 2nd or 3rd grade on the date of their 3000 day birthday. Your 3000 day birthday is on February 8, 1974.

Tween

We hear the word tween a lot these days. It is the time before you are a teenager, but after you are done playing with the silly kids toys! Your official tween time starts at age 10 and ends when you become a teenager. The date of your first day as a tween is on November 22, 1975.

Teenager

You're a teenager! You are no longer a child. This is a when a lot of changes happen emotionally, physically, with how people treat you, and with your level of personal responsibilities. You become a teenager on November 22, 1978.

5000 days old

Your 5000 day old birthday is a few months before your big 14th birthday. This day is a good day to have a party if you can't wait for your 14th birthday party. Your 5000 day birthday is on August 1, 1979.

Sweet 16

This is a big day for people born on November 22, 1965. You can get your Driver's License and this is also the day you are allowed to get a job so you can pay for gas. You are 16 years old on November 22, 1981.

18 Years old

Many consider you an adult at age 18. You can do stuff like vote or serve your country. But don't bring out the champagne yet - you have to wait another three years to drink alcohol. You are 18 years old on November 22, 1983.

21 Years old

OK. Now you can bring out the champagne! You are probably almost done with college, considering moving out of your parents' nest for good, and getting a real job. Welcome to reality! You are 21 years old on November 22, 1986.

10,000 days old

You are 27+ years old at this time. Do you still party? If so, this may be a good excuse to do so. Your 10,000 day birthday is on April 9, 1993.

30 Years old

Many feel this is the birthday when they transition from young to old. Are you married yet? Do you have children? Your biological clock is ticking fast now. You are 30 years old on November 22, 1995.

40 Years old

OK. At this point you're officially not young any more. You probably have lots of responsibilities with kids and a job and a house. Some people have a hard time with this birthday and are depressed, because they see this as the half-point of their life. You are 40 years old on November 22, 2005.

The BIG 50

You have lived half a century! You have seen it all and done it all, yet you feel happy, because the kids have moved out, you are working less and playing more, and you are looking forward to retirement. You are 50 years old on November 22, 2015.

Retirement

The Social Security Administration changes the age when you can get retirement benefits now and then, but as a general rule, you can start receiving partial benefits at age 62 and max benefits at 67 years old. You are 62 years old on November 22, 2027 and 67 years old on November 22, 2032.

25,000 days old

Yeah, yeah, we here at Research Maniacs are obsessed with "number of days birthdays". Anyway, you have to live for 68+ years before you can celebrate this one! Your 25,000 day birthday is on May 4, 2034.

That's it!

That's your life! However, if you live for a really, really long time, you may also be interested to know that you have to live until September 7, 2239 to celebrate your 100,000 day birthday and your 100th year birthday is on November 22, 2065.

This page describes very generally the life of a person born on November 22, 1965 in America. We know all people are different and all lives are different. This is simply made for entertainment and gives you some interesting numbers and dates to think about.
